<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1175.106416.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Dyscritulus europaeus sp. nov. holotype female A head B antenna C scape, pedicel, first and second flagellomere D mesonotum (= mesoscutum) - dorsal aspect E propodeum - dorsal aspect F petiole - dorsal aspect G ovipositor sheaths - lateral aspect H fore wing. Scale bars: 200 µm (A, D, E); 500 µm (B, H); 100 µm (C, F, G)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/894273" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1175.106416.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Dyscritulus europaeus sp. nov. paratype male A head B antenna C scape, pedicel, first and second flagellomere D mesonotum (= mesoscutum) - dorsal aspect E propodeum - dorsal aspect F petiole - dorsal aspect G genitalia - ventral aspect H fore wing. Scale bars: 200 µm (A, D); 500 µm (B, H); 100 µm (C, E, F, G)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/894274" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1175.106416.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Aphid mummies of the new species, Dyscritulus europaeus sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/894275" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

